JOHANNESBURG – According to Forbes Marvel’s Black Panther comic book blockbuster has raked in a gross of $1-billion worldwide in its fourth weekend. The movie has surpassed movies like The Force Awakens, which earned $42-million in 2016 and Spider-Man with only $45-million. READ: 'Black Panther' on record-setting prowl across North America There are predictions that the movie may be ranked as the seventh-biggest unadjusted domestic grosser of all time. Black Panther is listed as the 33rd movie to lead the $1-billion in unregulated global earnings alongside movies such as Iron Man 3, Captain America: Civil War and The Avengers. eNCA